abstract: The progressive leaders Pete Buttigieg and Stacey Abrams are confronting the hypocrisy of the religious right.
snippet: The progressive leaders Pete Buttigieg and Stacey Abrams are confronting the hypocrisy of the religious right.
lead_paragraph: We know that slaveholders in the American South used Scripture to justify keeping their fellow humans in bondage. They could find no words from Christ on this, for there are no words from him. Just a line in the New Testament from mere mortals presuming to speak for him.

snippet: James changed the literary landscape with her blockbuster erotica trilogy, “Fifty Shades of Grey.” Now she is trying something (sort of) new.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — E L James does not like speaking to journalists, who often want to know deeply personal things, like how much money she makes and whether she has a sex dungeon in her basement.

abstract: In a struggling neighborhood with a vibrant history, Titus Kaphar found a home for himself. Now he’s creating a center there to nurture emerging artists.
snippet: In a struggling neighborhood with a vibrant history, Titus Kaphar found a home for himself. Now he’s creating a center there to nurture emerging artists.
lead_paragraph: NEW HAVEN — Like many town-and-gown cities, New Haven is a community of parallel narratives. There is the storied Elm City of Yale University, a place of carillon bell towers, leaded glass windows and lush quadrangles behind iron gates.

abstract: From his beginnings as a teenage hacker in Australia to his arrest this week in London, the WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange has been a deeply divisive figure.
snippet: From his beginnings as a teenage hacker in Australia to his arrest this week in London, the WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange has been a deeply divisive figure.
lead_paragraph: The shaky video clips of Julian Assange’s arrest flashed around the world on Thursday, the white-bearded prophet of the age of leaks being hauled by unsmiling security officers to a gray van marked Police.

abstract: Finau kept a ball signed by Billy Casper, the 1970 champion, in his bag during the opening round. Casper had offered encouragement to Finau when he was taking up golf.
snippet: Finau kept a ball signed by Billy Casper, the 1970 champion, in his bag during the opening round. Casper had offered encouragement to Finau when he was taking up golf.
lead_paragraph: Tony Finau put a lucky 13th ball in his bag for his opening round of one-under-par 71 on Thursday at the Masters.

snippet: Uber, like many other tech companies, is using a few creative terms to describe its business. We’ll try to translate them for you.
lead_paragraph: It’s a timeworn tradition for technology companies to resort to an array of jargon and technical terms to describe their operations — especially if they’re not making a profit.

abstract: Shows about Leonard Cohen, instruments, punk graphics and punk sexual energy highlight the bonds between listeners and creators.
snippet: Shows about Leonard Cohen, instruments, punk graphics and punk sexual energy highlight the bonds between listeners and creators.
lead_paragraph: A man’s voice recites lines from a poem as fantastical low-resolution images of cityscapes are projected on a screen in a darkened room. “When I couldn’t sleep/I learned to write,” we hear him say. “I learned to write/what might be read/on nights like this/by one like me.”

abstract: At the tiny Ecuadorean Embassy, he ran WikiLeaks, held news conferences, rode his skateboard in the halls and hosted visitors like Pamela Anderson.
snippet: At the tiny Ecuadorean Embassy, he ran WikiLeaks, held news conferences, rode his skateboard in the halls and hosted visitors like Pamela Anderson.
lead_paragraph: The spectacle of Julian Assange, bearded and haggard, resisting arrest while London police officers dragged him through the street, punctuated the end of seven confounding years inside the Ecuadorean Embassy, where he lived with his cat in a small corner room as the world’s most famous self-proclaimed political refugee.

lead_paragraph: Despite a turbulent week in which he was accused by several women of inappropriate physical contact, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. remains popular among Iowa Democrats and leads a new poll that also indicates Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., is on the rise.
